description: For sale in our Detroit Showroom is the beautiful fully restored 1969 Ford Mustang Coupe. This beautiful Mustang will steal the show from its contenders! With a very bright Wimbledon White finish on its recently restored exterior it is hard not to see this beauty rolling by! The interior is a beautifully restored Black vinyl with Hi-Back bucket seats center console and being completely restored recently this interior looks as good as the day it was new. This 1969 Coupe is powered by a monster 302 CID V8 engine driven by the Ford C-4 automatic transmission and backed by the Ford 8"?  posi traction rear end. Do not miss your chance to own one of Americas most desirable muscle cars! You can hear this stallion coming from blocks away with the new headers and dual exhaust system on it! Be the roar everyone is talking about in the neighborhood! This Mustang is a great buy having a list of new parts a mile long and with the recent restoration which includes new painless wiring system  rebuilt heads the fuel system was redone the interior and suspension and steering with less than 5000 miles on the car since completion. Options on this beautiful Mustang for sale are: AM/FM radio with cassette player vinyl interior alloy wheels raised white letter radial tires and seat belts. For additional information on the clean and mean 1969 Ford Mustang for sale in our Detroit showroom please contact us at 313-982-3100 to view the car in more depth and a HD video please visit us on the web at www.GatewayClassicars.com

Up for sale in our Houston Showroom is this classic 1969 Ford Mustang Grande.  1969 saw the addition of the third restyling of the Mustang with more heft to the body with it being extended almost 4 inches ad the width increased by a half an inch.  The Grande edition was also a new edition as a luxury model that featured a softer ride extra sound deadening material added to the car as well as a deluxe interior with wood trim.  This one is powered by a 351 CiD V8 Windsor motor that runs strong & healthy throughout the power band.   The car in an M code car and originally came with a 390 V8.  The extremely popular 351 is paired to a C4 3-speed automatic transmission that shifts smoothly up & down through the gears.  The engine bay is clean and rust free.   All wires and components are neatly mounted and placed & it does have Ford polished valve covers & air cleaner.  The car also has dual exhaust. The exterior of the car is in very nice condition.  The paint is very nice and is free from any dings dents or major scratches.  The car does not have a very glossy finish but it is that of a very nice driver & still shows well.  The body panel gaps are even and the body is straight & true.  The polished trim is nice as well and doesn"??t require any attention.  The bumpers grill emblems & glass are also in very nice shape and are ready to roll.  The vinyl top is also in fantastic condition and is free from tears or blemishes.  Keeping the authentic classic look of the car is the original Ford hub cap wheels that are wrapped in newer radial tires that have plenty of life in them.  The interior is in excellent condition and is great looking on the Grande edition.  The vinyl & cloth seats are in superb condition and are comfortable.  The carpet dash door panels & headliner follow suit and are all in very nice shape.   The deluxe interior trim on the car is much different & unique when almost every other mustang on the market with the same basic look.   So it separates itself from the market with that factor.   The car is rust free and it was well cared for over the years.   The trunk is very clean as well.  The car looks just as good underneath it as it does on top.  New suspension & bushings are evident.  Car is believed to have original miles but it is not documented.  Options on this car include; power brakes power steering AM/FM with cassette white wall tires & more.
